USA Overall

As of yesterday, there has been a total of 23,612,055 cases of COVID-19 in the USA. This is a change of 240,925 (1.03%) new cases since the day prior. The 7 day moving average is currently 2.372e+05 new cases which is a 0.53% change since the day prior and -8.38% change since the week prior. The immediate trend is heading downward. Based on the addition of yesterdays data, yesterday was not an inflection point (days since last inflection point: 2 > 2021-01-14).

7-day moving average of new cases in the US (2020-01-21 to 2021-01-15)

References

ICU stress definitions:

  • low: less than 10% of ICU Usage
  • moderate: 10-29% of ICU Usage
  • high: 30-59% of ICU Usage
  • extreme: greater than 60% of ICU Usage

Inpatient stress definitions:

  • low: less than 5% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • moderate: 5-9% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • high: 10-19% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
  • extreme: greater than 20% of hospital beds occupied by COVID-19 patients
